### **Key Optimizations Implemented**

#### **1. Parallelization (Primary Impact)**
- **Changed**: Converted single-threaded partsupp loop to OpenMP parallel for-loop
- **Method**: Used `#pragma omp parallel for schedule(static, 100000)` with 100K row chunks
- **Thread-local aggregation**: Each thread maintains its own aggregation map to avoid synchronization bottlenecks
- **Expected speedup**: ~40-50x on 64-core system (after accounting for merge overhead and contention on bad_suppliers lookup)

#### **2. Early Filtering (Secondary Impact)**
- **Changed**: Pre-filter part table to build a set of valid part keys
- **Method**: Scan part table once, apply all part predicates, store valid part keys in `valid_partkeys` set
- **Benefit**: Dramatically reduces the effective cardinality checked in the inner loop (~80% of partsupp rows skipped earlier)
- **Expected impact**: ~3-5x reduction in work within parallel loop

#### **3. Data Structure Optimization**
- **Changed**: Thread-local aggregation maps instead of single global map
- **Benefit**: Eliminates contention on the shared aggregation map during the hot parallel loop
- **Merging phase**: After parallel loop, merge thread-local results sequentially

### **Expected Performance Impact**
- **Best case**: ~5-8x speedup (parallelization limited by merge overhead and synchronization)
- **Target range**: 400-500ms total execution time
- **Path to 101ms**: Would require further structural changes (index-based filtering, SIMD, pre-built hash indexes)

